description: In a secret bar within the city where magic is used to keep the peace, heroes and villains gather to enjoy a pint and talk about their days. But what happens when the magical barriers that prevent fighting are dropped and a building full of heroes and villains confront each other all at once? Knight and Squire have to save both friend and foe in this tale from the 6-issue miniseries from writer Paul Cornell (ACTION COMICS) and artist Jimmy Broxton (THE UNWRITTEN).
name: TPB
Paperinik e i super poteri problematici

description: A group of Moldovan immigrants reaches New Sulina, a village built in the swamps of the Mississippi Delta by their countrymen, finding it abandoned, and the prey of mysterious supernatural phenomena. It's up to Zagor and Cico, arrived in Louisiana in the footsteps of Velasquez, to solve the riddle.
name: Il villaggio del mistero

description: A dramatic night falls on the abandoned village in the swamps of the Mississippi Delta. Incredible Poltergeist phenomena are unleashed in the eyes of Zagor and Cico, terrorizing the settlers that came from Europe, and death is lurking in the trees that surround the town. As fear grips the hearts, only Zagor dares to face the mysterious presences that, from the dark recesses where they lie, cast warnings and signals...
name: Oscure presenze

description: Once in New Orleans on the trail of Velasquez, Zagor and Cico are unable to prevent this man to embark on a ship bound for Veracruz. The Spirit with the Hatchet, however, discovers that the pirate Jean Lafitte was captured by Mexican authorities while smuggling weapons along the coasts of Yucatan, and risks the gallows with all its crew. So, Zagor decides to leave for Mexico together with Denise Lafitte, to help her save her father (to whom he owes his life), at the same time continuing the hunt for Velasquez.
name: I bassifondi di New Orleans

description: Zagor and Cico land in Veracruz along with Denise, who wants to free his father, the pirate Jean Lafitte, imprisoned by the Mexicans on charges of smuggling weapons for the rebels. Zagor tries to track down Richter and Velasquez, who, in turn, came to Mexico in search of a lost city in the Yucatan jungle. There lies an ancient hidden treasure guarded by an impenetrable swamp, and by mysterious warriors who have taken up the use of human sacrifice and are preparing to spark a revolt of the indigenous peoples of southern Mexico.
name: Sulla pista del nemico

description: On the trail of the mysterious warriors who kidnapped Jean Lafitte, Zagor, Cico and Denise discover a new city called Tenochtitlan, hidden in the marshes of the Yucatan, where people still live according to the customs of the ancient Aztecs. Cuitluhuac, the ruler of the city, instigated by the shaman Izcalli, resumed the custom of human sacrifice to the gods and wants to restore the Aztec empire by unleashing a riot of the native nauhatl people. For that, he is getting firearms with the help of two British smugglers. Meanwhile, Richter and Velasquez, escorted by the Mexican banda Rojo gang, are moving into the jungle ...
name: Nella giungla dello Yucatan

description: The Spirit with the Hatchet is in Mexico chasing his enemies, the archaeologist Richter and his lieutenant Velasquez, who are looking for the city of New Tenochtitlan, believing that it hides something mysterious and infinitely precious. Meanwhile, at the court of Cuitluhuac, the cruel and bloodthirsty ruler of what should become the capital of the New Aztec Empire, someone plots in secret to overthrow the king, thinking that is leading the city towards certain destruction.
name: La cittÃ  nella palude

description: Zagor and Cico, penetrated one of the palaces of New Tenochtitlan to save Jean Lafitte, captured by the Aztecs, are then captured, while Denise manages to escape. Meanwhile, Richter and Velasquez, are about to make their entrance into the city in search of a mysterious artifact of Atlantean origin
name: Piramide di sangue

description: The attempt to assassinate Empress Oshman Leira risks to throw the political system of the Gonthar Galaxy into chaos. The old animosity between the various noble families return to sour and only the diplomacy of the League of Planets could achieve a peaceful solution. But who is the architect of the plot to destabilize the empire? Major Helen Sheldon, with the help of the entire team of the Argo asteroid, has little time to unravel the intrigue and capture the culprits.
name: Il destino dell'impero

description: Charles Xavier is dead - killed twenty years in the past during a freak time-travel accident - and the world that has arisen in his absence is dark and dangerous indeed. The Darwinian conqueror Apocalypse rules with an iron fist, ruthlessly enforcing his dictum that only the strong shall survive - and in Apocalypse's long shadow, hidden among a downtrodden humankind, are a group of ragtag freedom fighters led by Xavier's oldest friend, Magneto: the Amazing X-Men! When Bishop, last survivor of the true Marvel Universe, locates the X-Men and explains how the world went wrong, these embittered mutants and their tenuous allies must risk everything - and undertake a dangerous and multi-pronged quest - to put things right! The comics event of 1995 is collected in one deluxe oversized hardcover! Collecting UNCANNY X-MEN (1963) #320-321, X-MEN (1991) #40-41, CABLE (1993) #20, X-MEN ALPHA, AMAZING X-MEN #1-4, ASTONISHING X-MEN (1995) #1-4, FACTOR X #1-4, GAMBIT & THE X-TERNALS #1-4, GENERATION NEXT #1-4, WEAPON X (1995) #1-4, X-CALIBRE #1-4, X-MAN #1-4, X-MEN OMEGA, AGE OF APOCALYPSE: THE CHOSEN and X-MEN ASHCAN #2.
name: X-Men: Age of Apocalypse Omnibus

description: Archie as Pureheart the Powerful in "Postage Due" - When a disgruntled ex-postal worker turns his aggression towards those who formerly employed him, it's up to Pureheart to stop him! Holding Mr. Lodge responsible, the wealthy industrialist is put in harm's way when the villain seeks revenge on him. Will Pureheart be able to thwart the anti-mail man before he can sabotage the postal service for good?
name: Postage Due

The Infestation threatens all of America, and its evil seems unstoppable as it infects everything in its path. Tobias Muldoon is called upon to help the Autobots find a solution, and he knows the perfect man for the jobâNikola Tesla! Together they attempt to re-activate Optimus Prime, but it's unclear if he will be able to turn the tide in an increasingly hopeless situation!

description:
Back Blurb

Sex, food, money, death and a floor show

JANE does bad conceptual art in the Village. That's not her only problem. Oversexed CANNIBAL SPACE CHICKS want to eat her boyfriend ALLEN. And a savage cabal of BUSINESSMEN -- corporate monsters in a very real sense -- want her to spy against the Space Chick! Meanwhile, her boyfriend's in bed with a pair of seven-foot-tall Chicks who want his body in the worst way. Secret sex rituals, global conspiracies! Cult orgies and gruesome raygun battles! Cornfield orgies and office politics! What's a post-postmodern girl to do?

description: Trap him in Hell or trap him in humanity, Dracula will fight to the finish, fang and claw! But after centuries of being haunted by his demonic daughter, the Transylvanian tyrant faces an even worse family skeleton: A son who's an absolute angel! Plus the menaces of Dr. Sun, Dr. Frost, and Sorcerer Supreme Dr. Strange! Guest-starring Blade, Hannibal King, and the Silver Surfer! Collecting TOMB OF DRACULA #32-70, GIANT-SIZE DRACULA #5 and DR. STRANGE #14.
This issue features "They'll Do It Every Time" cartoons.

volume.name: Brand New Cartoons by Jimmy Hatlo

description: Bruce Paley turned 18 in 1967 during the Summer of Love, putting him on the front lines of the late-1960s youth movement. Paley's tumultuous journey took him from being a Jack Kerouac-loving hippie in the 1960s, on the road with his 17-year-old girlfriend, living in a car, and crashing with armed Black Panthers at the infamous 1968 Democratic National Convention, to hanging out at Max's Kansas City, hanging with the likes of rock star Johnny Thunders, and frequenting Times Square's seedy brothels - a journey that mirrored the changing times as the optimism of the '60s gave way to the nihilism of the punk years. Over a dozen years, Bruce crossed paths with hippies, violent cops, rednecks, rock stars, and Black Panthers...and ended up a heroin addict for much of the 1970s. These stories are vividly brought to life in Giraffes in My Hair (A Rock 'N' Roll Life) by the compelling visual storytelling of Bruce's partner, the cartoonist Carol Swain. Swain's trademark visual approach to comics, typified by exquisitely composed panels that vividly capture both anomie and pathos, is perfectly suited to dramatizing Paley's life during that confusing, tumultuous period of American history - a life lived in the countercultural margins, amidst personal chaos and social dissolution. Swain's storytelling rhythms are contemplative and breathes inner life into Paley's turbulent stories, creating a perceptive prism to view the vast possibilities and endless pitfalls as experienced by a kid growing up in America in the late 1960s and early '70s.

volume.name: Giraffes in My Hair: A Rock 'n' Roll Life

description:
In Ancient Rome, Lilith enters the arena with the gladiators!

Lilith is in imperial Rome, during the brief reign of Lucius Aurelius Commodus. It is the apotheosis of circus games period: in Flavian amphitheater - known to history as the "Colosseum" - those sentenced to death were executed in public, expert hunters faced wild beasts from around the world and the Roman gladiators also were measured in duels to the death. The new target of the time traveler is Narcissus, a former gladiator and personal coach of the emperor . To reach the bearer of spiromorfh and to accomplish her mission, Lilith must enter the arena and become the new star of the Roman public.
name: La signora dei giochi

description: Hell demands its revenge. A demoniacal painting, an exhibition of disturbing wonders, a diabolical elisir â these are the weapons by means of which Harlan will be surrounded, defeated and dragged off to put him on the side of Evil. Caleb, Tesla and Kurjak are powerless against the craftiness of cunning Nergal, the head of the secret police of Hell, and his agent Belyalis. But whose side will Nikolaus be on?
name: L'elisir del diavolo

For Bobby Quintana, an ambiable cop belonging to the Drug Seizure Squad, things have been getting even worse since a ferocious âMilitiaâ of undead have entered the fray. Luckily, our heroes arrive to give him a helping handâ¦

Alter Ego presents a big Batman issue, featuring an unused Golden Age cover by definitive Dark Knight artist Dick Sprang! Headlining this bat-centric issue is a Shel Dorf interview with Sprang and Jim Mooney! Plus there's rare and unseen Batman art by Bob Kane, Jerry Robinson, Win Mortimer, Shelly Moldoff, Charles Paris, and others! Part II of the Tony Tallarico interview, conducted by Jim Amash!

Two retirees of Gand, the Fleming Adriaen de Kremer and the Wallon ThÃ¨o Durand, are bound by a long-standing friendship that goes way back, all the way back to their childhood in fact. But suspicion insinuates itself between the pair when, one by one, their old buddies from their schooldays are killed gruesomely by a mysterious murderer. Then Adriaen remembers the waking nightmare he had one night long ago, when for the first time he saw the shadowsâ¦

description: With the help of Nikolaus and the crow Kavka, Harlan brings to light a manuscript from the realm of arcane magic and personally re-lives some of the experiences his father Draka went through during the Thirty Years War, the long conflict that ravaged Europe in the Seventeenth century. For instance, that was the time when Draka had to contend with the ferocious hordes of Wehrwolfe, Werewolves, up there in the wild moorland of northern Saxonyâ¦
name: I lupi mannari

description: In the Wild West, Ross Kriegerâs ruthless scalp-hunters, whoâve been dead over a century, are reincarnated in the body of a group of cowboys and then they exact their revenge on those who delivered them up to the Apaches. Harlan Draka and his friends, whoâve traveled to Arizona on the tracks of the Master of the Night IxtlÃ¡n, help Johnny Young Eagle and his tribe against the band of living dead. But thereâs just one small problem: since the members of this band are - true to their name - already dead, they canât be killed!
name: La banda dei morti viventi

description: On the San Carlos reservation, horror is set to arrive! More and more decomposed, and ever more invincible, the six scalp-hunters want to perpetrate a carnage on the hated Apaches. Against them, as well as Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak, thereâs also the young guy called Johnny Young Eagle and an aging Catholic priest. Charlene, Johnnyâs ex-girl-friend, and Tyree, his cousin, fall into the hands of the living deadâ¦ The tribal police on the reservation are powerless against them. How will our heroes manage to stop them? And who is the traitor that tried to have Johnny killed by the scalp-hunters?
name: Arizona killers

description: King Kong at the "Manhattan", live mummies at the "Luxor", dragons at the "Camelot", deadly Harlequins at the "Rialto"â¦ Whatâs going on at the luxury hotels of Las Vegas? Who is intent on causing harm to tourism and to the bigwigs who hold the reins of the city? And why, for some time now, in New York and elsewhere as well, have they been dragging up corpses whose bellies are riddled with knife slashes, an unmistakable sign of the homicidal art of the legendary gangster Bugsy Siegel?
name: Vegas!

description: Zagor and Cico cross the ocean aboard the ship "Dragoon" of Captain Honest Joe, along with old and new friends, to continue the hunt for the evil Professor Richter, headed toward a remote island that was thousands of years before the colony of Atlantis
name: Ultima Thule

description: The Maelstrom, the immense and legendary ocean vortex off Norway that swallows ships and vessels, is only the first of the terrible dangers that await the pursuers of Professor Richter. The silent servant of Richter, the colossal Bork, kidnaps Felix, and while Zagor's friends are grappling with the inhabitants of the Faroe Islands, the Spirit with the Hatchet, alone, follows the "Erebus" and lands on the stormy coasts of Iceland.
name: Discesa nel Maelstrom
